CANVAS

Pre-scanner

We define the pre-scanner as all of the components preceding an active scanning element. In this case the beam is passing approximately through the center of the cage elements, and the alignment becomes particularly simple.

In the pre-scanner, we recognize two parts. In the first one, the properties of the beam, such as the power, polarization, and beam diameter are set. The goal of the second part is to steer the beam to the entrance of the scanner and is consists mostly of the periscope.

  • Beam forming
  • Periscope

The components (divided into modules) necessary to build the NL-2p1 pre-scanner can be found in the pre-scanner tab of the NL-2p1_asmbly.xlsx.
